The Asset Forfeiture Unit is expected to confiscate millions of rand worth of assets from Edwin Sodi. eNCA reporter Aviwe Mtila has more. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Blackhead Consulting director Edwin Sodi could soon find his choice of transport severely limited. The Asset Forfeiture Unit is expected to confiscate millions of rand worth of assets from him. These include a house in Bryanston and a range of luxury cars. READ:Â AFU seizes assets of asbestos project suspects Sodi and six others appeared in court last week. They've been charged in connection with the R255-million asbestos project in the Free State. Sodi testified at the state capture inquiry that he'd made contributions to the ANC. But he denied his donations were linked to the various government tenders he received.